result.execSummary:
All charges against Terrence C Cunningham in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Terrence C Cunningham is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Status conference on October 25, 2022 at 09:30 am.

[ml] Case called at 9:09AM
Defendant Terrence C Cunningham does not appear. ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
This file is scheduled for a Status Conference, however the Defendant does not appear.

The State advises that the Defendant has not appeared in Illinois.
The State advises that the DA's Office has the governor's warrant in hand and that the Defendant would be taken into custody.

ADA Teuber advises that the Defendant appeared at the DA's Office on 06/01

The Court issues a Bench Warrant, returnable to any Jefferson County Magistrate,

The Clerk advises that they have just received word that the Defendant is in the courthouse and coming down to appear. The Court recesses briefly so that the Defendant may appear.

recess 9:11AM

---------------------------------------

reconvene 9:13AM

The Defendant now appears without counsel. All other appearances remain the same.

The Defendant vacates any orders it made regarding the Bench Warrant. 

The Defendant makes a statement regarding the warrant and interstate communication.
The Defendant requests that another hearing be scheduled so that the extradition matters.

The Court commits the Defendant to the custody of the Jefferson County Sheriff's Office so that the governor's warrant may be executed.
The Court orders the $2,000.00 Cash Bond be returned to whoever posted it.
A deputy present makes a statement regarding the warrant.

The Defendant is taken into custody.

recess 9:21AM
Status conference on June 3, 2022 at 09:00 am.

[ml] Case called at 8:49AM
Defendant Terrence C Cunningham in court, without counsel. ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.

The Defendant advises that he has contacted the original issuing agency of the warrant.
The Defendant advises that he wishes to waive extradition, as well as his right to counsel.

The Court finds the waiver to be knowingly and intelligently waived.
There is discussion regarding the issue of bond and extradition.
The Defendant advises that he will not be waiving extradition if it means that he will go into custody in Jefferson County.

The Court recesses briefly to discuss this matter with the Clerk's Office. 

recess 8:57AM

--------------------------------------------

reconvene 9:01AM

The Court clarifies questions that the Defendant had, including cooperating with McClean County.
The State proposes another alternative in which the Defendant returns to Illinois to clear up the warrant himself.
The Court adopts the State's proposal.

The Court finds good cause to extend this hearing 60 days and sets this matter over.
The Court advises that this hearing may fall off its calendar if the Defendant takes care of the matter in Illinois and the State dismisses the charges in this file.

recess 9:06AM

NEXT: Further Proceedings on 06/03 at 9:00AM with in person appearances
